            "id": "0430546575464eb1a4e95",
            "questionText": "A hospital receives a shipment of Iodine-131 ($!$I-131$!$) with an initial activity ($!$A_0$!$) of 50 mCi. $!$I-131$!$ is used for thyroid treatments. Given that the half-life ($!$T_{1/2}$!$) of $!$I-131$!$ is approximately 8 days and considering the random and spontaneous nature of radioactive decay, what will be the activity of the $!$I-131$!$ sample after 24 days? Use the formula $!$A = A_0 e^{-\\lambda t}$!$ to find the activity.",
